3. what is the difference between CSS2 ans CSS3?\par
\par
Ans- In CSS2, everything is present in a single document while CSS3 is categorized into multiple sections called modules.\par
Graphics-related features such as Box-shadow or Border-radius, flexbox, etc. can be found which are absent in case of CSS2.\par
Properties such as background-position, background-image, and background-repeat styles can be helpful for using multiple background images in a single webpage.\par
CSS3 versions support many new browsers.\par
CSS3 introduces many new selectors in the form of pseudo-elements and pseudo-classes.\par
